
Analysed KPI keys:

1)Total number of orders
2)Total revenue generated
3)Top 5 best-selling products
4)Average Order Value (AOV)
5)Revenue by product category
6)Monthly sales trend
7)Top customers by total spend
8)Orders by customer location
9)total quantity of product sold


Solutions:

1) Total Number of Orders:
   SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT TransactionID) AS total_orders
   FROM ecommerce_sales_data;


2) Total revenue generated:
   SELECT 
    SUM(Quantity * Price * (1 - Discount)) AS total_revenue
  FROM ecommerce_sales_data;


3) Top 5 best-selling products:
  SELECT *
  FROM ( 
       SELECT ProductID,
              SUM(Quantity) AS total_quantity_sold
       FROM ecommerce_sales_data
       GROUP BY ProductID
       ORDER BY total_quantity_sold DESC
 )
 WHERE ROWNUM <= 5;


4) Average Order Value (AOV): 
    SELECT
    ROUND(
         SUM(Quantity * Price * (1 - Discount)) / COUNT(DISTINCT TransactionID),2) 
       AS avg_order_value
   FROM ecommerce_sales_data;


5) Revenue by product category:
   SELECT 
     ProductCategory,
     SUM(Quantity * Price * (1 - Discount)) AS category_revenue
  FROM ecommerce_sales_data
  GROUP BY ProductCategory
 ORDER BY category_revenue DESC;


6) Monthly sales trend:
    SELECT 
        EXTRACT(MONTH FROM TransactionDate) AS month,
        SUM(Quantity * Price * (1 - Discount)) AS monthly_sales
   FROM ecommerce_sales_data
   GROUP BY EXTRACT(MONTH FROM TransactionDate)
   ORDER BY month;


7) Top customers by total spend:
    SELECT *
    FROM (
    SELECT 
    CustomerID,
   SUM(Quantity * Price * (1 - Discount)) AS total_spent
   FROM ecommerce_sales_data
   GROUP BY CustomerID
   ORDER BY total_spent DESC
   )
   WHERE ROWNUM <= 5;


8) Orders by Customer Location:
   SELECT  
    CustomerLocation,
    COUNT(DISTINCT TransactionID) AS total_orders
   FROM ecommerce_sales_data
   GROUP BY CustomerLocation
   ORDER BY total_orders DESC;


9)Total Quantity of Products Sold:
  SELECT 
    SUM(Quantity) AS total_products_sold
FROM ecommerce_sales_data;





